<br>
Basically, ND will give you 10% more hp's at most, based off your stamina. Obviously this will affect the better equipped mages more, since they will have higher STA values. I would like to know how many hp's you can really get from this skill, I imagine it wont be more than maybe 200-300 at best (with high stamina, would love to hear real numbers here).<br>
<br>
This is enough to maybe survive another round of combat at high level encounters. Not too impressive.<br>
<br>
Avoidance gives you a 10% higher chance to completely escape incoming damage. At very high levels this can mean a LOT of damage that doesnt hit you, when single melee rounds are 300, 400 or even more damage.<br>
<br>
So my impression is that avoidance is a superior skill to durability. Of course I might be wrong, and would love to hear reports of mages who have either or both skills.<br>
<br>
Izudin<br>
